node.text: As a professional skate photographer, the work of Anthony Acosta (@AAcostaa) has been featured in magazines worldwide. Inspired by the sense of community that a mini ramp brings, he worked with a group of friends to build a fully functioning darkroom. See more of these projects at vans.com/offthewall

node.text: @LizzieArmanto's accomplished a lot of firsts. First woman to do the loop, land a Transworld cover, and a lot of others for herself and for skateboarding. They all came with a battle that’s made her tougher on the inside. Hear Lizzie tell the behind the battle story for her @ThrasherMag ender here, then share your own memorable firsts with us by tagging us and #SkateboardersFirst in your posts. 📹: @Talkin_Schmit #GrossoForever

node.text:
Like our new Vans Skate Classics, skateboarders are tough on the inside. Whether it’s your first ever, or just a new one you’ve never done before, learning a trick is tough no matter who you are. What’s the one that took you a million tries? Share it with #SkateboardersFirst and @VansSkate so we can check it out & we might even share some of our favorites. 🏁 @AxelCrusher 
📹: @YerDone

Take a look inside the making of Alright, OK, with an intimate conversation between global signature team riders Elijah Berle (@BerleHaggard) and Gilbert Crockett (@CeeBlues) and acclaimed filmmaker Greg Hunt. Elijah Berle opens up about the challenges he has faced during the two years of making the film while Richmond native, Gilbert Crockett, shares his point of view on the art of creating video parts.

A video by @HuntFilmwork.

node.text:
Vans Skateboarding proudly presents Alright, OK, a new skate film featuring global signature team riders Elijah Berle and Gilbert Crockett, with a special guest appearance by Justin Henry. Directed by acclaimed filmmaker Greg Hunt—whose talent brought to life Vans’ first full-length skateboarding video, PROPELLER—Alright, OK is yet another masterpiece, encapsulating an epic labor of love by pro Elijah Berle, who worked tirelessly over two hard years to land arguably the best tricks of his career. Elijah shares the screen with Vans teammate and Richmond native, Gilbert Crockett, whose contrasting, eccentric style flows alongside Elijah’s timeless form like yin to yang.

Director Greg Hunt reunites the two for the first time since the release of Vans PROPELLER in 2015, finding skate spots from all over the globe in Australia, New Zealand, Spain, Portugal, New York and their home states of Virginia and California. Skateboarding has a gift of bringing together the most unlikely people from around the world, through the love of the simple act of rolling.

A video by Greg Hunt.

Cinematography by:Greg Hunt
Will Rosenstock
Cody Green
TJ Gaskill
Kevin O’Dell
Joseph Charlton

Learn more about the film at Vans.com/alrightok

node.text: grew up skating in ‪Columbus, Ohio‬ where he learned the value of putting in work and making each try count.
